history.content: I don't think this will be an issue; they'll have no issues adding you to Gradescope whenever you actually take it.

children.subject: Yeah, the Gradescopes of each semester edition of a class are separate from one another

history.content:
Hi, I was going through CS 188’s lectures from Fall 2019 when I saw the Gradescope invite code on one of the lecture slides.

I just wanted to play around with the homeworks so I tried it to see if it works. It did add me to 188’s Fall 2019 Gradescope but I now want to remove it if possible to avoid any issues that might come up if and when I actually take the class

Would this be problematic? I had no wrong intentions whatsoever, just wanted to explore something new now that the Spring semester’s almost ended

Any help/inputs would be appreciated, thank you!
history.subject: Accidentally added myself to previous semester’s Gradescope
